✅ Difference Between CSR (Client‑Side Rendering) and SSR (Server‑Side Rendering)

🔹 What is CSR (Client‑Side Rendering)?
In Client‑Side Rendering, the browser is responsible for rendering the page.
🔁 How it works
	1. Browser loads a minimal HTML file
	2. JavaScript bundle is downloaded
	3. JavaScript runs in the browser
	4. UI is rendered dynamically
✅ Pros
	• Smooth user interactions after initial load
	• Less load on the server
	• Suitable for dashboards and internal apps
❌ Cons
	• Slower first page load
	• Poor SEO (content not immediately available)
	• Blank screen until JS loads
📌 Example
Most Create React App projects use CSR by default.

🔹 What is SSR (Server‑Side Rendering)?
In Server‑Side Rendering, the server renders the HTML for each request and sends it to the browser.
🔁 How it works
	1. User requests a page
	2. Server renders full HTML
	3. Browser displays content immediately
	4. JavaScript hydrates the page for interactivity
✅ Pros
	• Faster first contentful paint
	• Better SEO
	• Content visible even with slow networks
❌ Cons
	• Higher server load
	• Slightly slower navigation after first load
	• More complex implementation
📌 Example
Next.js pages using getServerSideProps() use SSR.

⚖️ CSR vs SSR – Side‑by‑Side Comparison
Aspect	CSR	SSR
Rendering Location	Browser	Server
First Load	Slower	Faster
SEO	Weak	Strong
Server Load	Low	Higher
User Experience	Smooth after load	Stable from start
Best Use Case	Dashboards, Admin apps	Marketing, SEO pages

🧠 Interview‑Ready Answer (30 Seconds)
	CSR renders content in the browser after JavaScript loads, which can cause slower initial load and SEO issues.
	SSR renders HTML on the server before sending it to the browser, leading to faster first load and better SEO.
	In frameworks like Next.js, we choose CSR or SSR based on performance and business needs.

✅ When to Use What?
Use CSR when:
	• SEO is not important
	• App is user‑centric (dashboards)
	• Backend APIs already exist
Use SSR when:
	• SEO is critical
	• Content changes frequently
	• First page load performance matters

🔐 Real‑World Example
	• E‑commerce product page → SSR (SEO + fast load)
	• Admin panel → CSR (less SEO, more interaction)

